gnome-clipboard-daemon: gnome-clipboard-daemon (clipboard-daemon for GNOME :)
gnome-clipboard-daemon:
gnome-clipboard-daemon: GNOME Clipboard Daemon is a program that keeps
gnome-clipboard-daemon: the content of your X clipboard in memory, so
gnome-clipboard-daemon: the clipboard won' get lost even after you close
gnome-clipboard-daemon: the application you copied from. It's a daemon -
gnome-clipboard-daemon: it has no GUI. You start it and it'll run in the
gnome-clipboard-daemon: background and Just Work(tm).
